tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE RobotBlueprints (
  blueprint_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  blueprint_name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  robot_type VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  designer_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
  created_date TIMESTAMP NOT NULL
)

CREATE TABLE RobotBlueprints (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    blueprint_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    robot_type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    blueprint_data TEXT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE TABLE RobotVersions (
    version_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    blueprint_id INT REFERENCES RobotBlueprints(id),
    version_number INT NOT NULL,
    version_data TEXT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE TABLE RobotUsers (
    user_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR(100) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    password TEXT NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT now()
);

CREATE TABLE robot_versions (
  version_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  robot_id INT,
  version_number VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
  changes_description TEXT,
  date_published DATE,
  FOREIGN KEY(robot_id) REFERENCES robots(robot_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Parts (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  quantity INT,
  robot_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (robot_id) REFERENCES Robots (id)
);

CREATE TABLE Blueprints (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
  blueprint_data TEXT,
  robot_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (robot_id) REFERENCES Robots (id)
);

CREATE TABLE Versions (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  version_number INT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  blueprint_id INT,
  FOREIGN KEY (blueprint_id) REFERENCES Blueprints (id)
);
